              <entry>LO 1 </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Promotion of Health</emphasis>The learner is able to make informed decisions concerning personal, community and environmental health.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <emphasis effect="italics">We know this when the learner:</emphasis>
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>1.1 plans an action in which laws and/or policies for protecting environmental health are applied to address an environmental health issue;</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>1.2 critically analyses the causes of common diseases in relation to socio-economic and environmental factors;</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>1.4 indicates that he/she is able to take responsible and informed decisions on personal and environmental safety; and;</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>1.5 examines a health and safety issue related to violence, and proposes alternatives to violence as well as counter-strategies.</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
